title: LLD crash with polymorphization

labels.name: T-compiler
labels.description: Relevant to the compiler team, which will review and decide on the PR/issue.

labels.name: E-needs-mcve
labels.description: Call for participation: This issue needs a Minimal Complete and Verifiable Example

body:
While working on [this code](https://github.com/Kixiron/sruth/tree/1a71f373d63deb3e619f0a11a70606cbc26247eb) and using the `-Zpolymorphize` flag I managed to get `lld` to crash in a rather large way. Simply removing the `-Zpolymorphize` flag fixes the issue ### Meta `rustc --version --verbose`: ``` rustc 1.52.0-nightly (0148b971c 2021-02-18) binary: rustc commit-hash: 0148b971c921a0831fbf3357e5936eec724e3566 commit-date: 2021-02-18 host: x86_64-pc-windows-msvc release: 1.52.0-nightly LLVM version: 11.0.1 ```
